{
  "stem": "812.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And we had our furniture and linens and things of that that we were allowed to take out of Germany at that time, and everything was completely destroyed.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Then we were sent to Camp Westerbork in Holland, which is a transit camp where people from throughout Europe, and particularly from Holland, were brought.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Many of them were taken from their hiding places, and thousands of people were sent to Westerbork.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Westerbork was tolerable as a transit camp.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And we lived in barracks, but we were allowed to stay together as a family.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And life for us children was very [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] plain.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "We had nothing to do.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "It was stagnant.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And-- but we did have enough food to eat.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "We ate in a communal dining room.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And as I said, we had like a-- a one-bedroom little apartment within the barracks.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "So life was bearable.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And later on, though, as time went on, many, many more people came to Westerbork, and we had to share our apartment, which was fine.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "As far as food, it was simple and plain, but sufficient.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And I remember craving sweets, and we-- somebody who had come to us had brought [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] saccharine.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And I figured, well, saccharine's got to be specially good.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "So I took a handful of saccharine and thought I would satisfy my craving of sweets.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "It was not nearly as pleasant as I had hoped it would be, to say the least.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] we were in Westerbork until-- really from the very beginning of 1940 until January of 1944.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "It was at that time that people were sent from Westerbork to various concentration camps in Germany and Eastern Europe.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And we children really welcomed the change.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
